00:33:25.110 --> 00:33:28.090
So it's an exothermic reaction.

00:33:28.090 --> 00:33:30.600
So what temperature
would you want

00:33:30.600 --> 00:33:33.860
to use to get more products?

00:33:33.860 --> 00:33:36.060
Right, you want to
use low temperature,

00:33:36.060 --> 00:33:37.920
because that would
favor your products.

00:33:37.920 --> 00:33:42.570
But low temperature is
also sometimes not great,

00:33:42.570 --> 00:33:45.340
because it slows the
rate, which is bad.

00:33:45.340 --> 00:33:48.930
So the compromise temperature
that's used in this process

00:33:48.930 --> 00:33:51.120
is 500 degrees Celsius.

00:33:51.120 --> 00:33:52.470
So it's pretty hot.

00:33:52.470 --> 00:33:56.100
So this works, again, maximizing
the yield of products.

